# Embelleze Web Â· Codex Context

## Identity

Official site/webapp for Instituto Embelleze Trindade.

- Framework: Astro SSR
- Deploy: Railway direct build from `emb-trind/embelleze-web`
- Domain: `embelleze-bella.online`
- Primary goal: convert visitors into qualified WhatsApp conversations with Bella

## Required Reading

Before changing code, read the closest applicable docs:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `CONTEXT.md`
- `MEMORY.md`
- `SKILL.md`
- parent workspace docs when the task touches deploy, workspace, or service boundaries

This service belongs to the `embelleze-trdd` control plane, but it is its own repo.
Do not assume a monorepo contract beyond the parent `pnpm-workspace.yaml`.

## Operating Rules

- Keep `src/pages/index.astro` as a section importer only.
- Keep landing sections in `src/sections/`.
- Keep reusable UI in `src/components/`.
- Keep business/editable data in `src/content/`.
- Keep Bella orchestration in `src/lib/bella.ts`.
- Keep WhatsApp URL generation in `src/lib/whatsapp.ts`.
- Keep tracking names and helpers in `src/lib/tracking.ts`.
- VitÃ³ria is the site chat atendimento agent; Bella is the WhatsApp SDR handoff.
- Do not duplicate WhatsApp links, lead flow logic, or Bella prompt logic.
- Do not invent prices, offers, courses, testimonials, or commercial claims.
- Do not touch `.env`, secrets, tokens, private keys, or credentials.
- Do not expose phone numbers beyond masked/last-four patterns in logs.
- Public API routes must keep payload limits and rate limits.
- Prefer the smallest functional patch that preserves the current architecture.

## Lead And Messaging Flow

Active/known paths:

- Site form: `src/pages/api/leads.ts`
- Site chat: `src/pages/api/bella/chat.ts`
- WhatsApp Baileys inbound: `src/pages/api/whatsapp/webhook.ts`
- FlowPay payment webhook: `src/pages/api/payment/flowpay/webhook.ts`
- VitÃ³ria web prompt: `src/content/vitoria.web.md`

Important libraries:

- `src/lib/db.ts` persists and deduplicates leads/events
- `src/lib/probeltec.ts` syncs leads to CRM
- `src/lib/whatsapp-gateway.ts` sends WhatsApp responses through `neo-whatsapp-connect`
- `src/lib/phone.ts` normalizes and masks phone numbers
- `src/lib/redis.ts` stores Bella conversation history
- `src/lib/resend.ts` sends transactional email

The legacy WhatsApp provider has been removed from runtime. Do not reintroduce it without an explicit integration decision.

VitÃ³ria handoff rule: when the site chat needs WhatsApp, it must trigger the canonical `wa.me` flow only. Do not add WhatsApp Business deep links, app-store fallbacks, Play Store links, or alternate WhatsApp URLs.

## Section Contract

Every landing section should:

- Have one clear conversion role
- Be readable on mobile
- Be isolated enough to work without another section
- Use a CTA only when it helps the user's next action
- Avoid business data hardcoded in markup when `src/content/` is a better source

Core sections:

- `Hero`
- `BellaIntro`
- `LocalImpact`
- `CourseOffer`
- `CoursesGrid`
- `ObjectionBreak`
- `SocialProof`
- `FutureSimulator`
- `MapPreview`
- `FinalCTA`
- `WhatsAppFloat`

`DiscountTicket` exists but is intentionally disabled unless a campaign requires it.

## Commands

Use pnpm. The parent workspace also uses pnpm.

```sh
make help
make dev
make check
make build
make validate
make smoke
```

Fallback without Make:

```sh
pnpm check
pnpm build
pnpm dev -- --host 127.0.0.1 --port 4321
```

## Validation

For code changes, run:

```sh
make validate
```

For local runtime smoke after starting the dev server, run:

```sh
make smoke
```

For documentation-only or context-only changes, at least inspect the final diff
and confirm no unrelated user changes were modified.
